  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nAfter discussions with Supranational last week, we now know that BLST requires at least [SSSE3](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SSSE3), even when compiled without `-march=native`.\r\n\r\nWe could resolve this either by:\r\n\r\n* Switching to Milagro at compile time if we detect the absence of SSSE3 using the `target_features` cfg flag: https://doc.rust-lang.org/reference/attributes/codegen.html#available-features, or\r\n* Pushing BLST to include a scalar implementation of SHA256, so that SSSE3 is no longer required\r\n\r\nI think option (2) is preferable, as it will allow us to distribute just two binaries instead of three i.e. [ADX, no ADX] instead of [ADX, SSSE3, Neither].\r\n",
